Croatia [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group I|qualified]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]] undefeated for their first five matches.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/modric-unwilling-to-back-croatia-coach-outburst-world-cup/1kn4k8vrvygl11lm9o5etdxf6v|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007211028/http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/modric-unwilling-to-back-croatia-coach-outburst-world-cup/1kn4k8vrvygl11lm9o5etdxf6v|archive-date=7 October 2017|title=Real Madrid star Luka Modrić unwilling to back Croatia coach in outburst |work=Goal.com|access-date=24 October 2017}}</ref> Two defeats to Iceland and Turkey, as well as a draw against [[Finland national football team|Finland]], led to a public outcry that ousted manager Čačić.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.slobodnadalmacija.hr/sport/domaci-nogomet/clanak/id/510853/dosje-ante-cacic-niti-zna-niti-autoritet-ima|title=Dosje Ante Čačić: Niti zna, niti autoritet ima...|work=Slobodna Dalmacija|access-date=24 October 2017|language=hr-HR}}</ref> He was replaced by [[Zlatko Dalić]], who formally qualified the team with a 2–0 win against Ukraine,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/video/1066494019594|title=Ukraine vs. Croatia: 2017 UEFA World Cup Qualifying Highlights (VIDEO)|work=Fox Sports|access-date=24 October 2017}}</ref> and a 4–1 win with Greece, on aggregate, during a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|playoff round]] in the first leg in Zagreb.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sport.hrt.hr/414518/htv-1-2045-dodatne-kvalifikacije-hrvatska-grcka|title=[VIDEO] Rapsodija Vatrenih u Maksimiru, u Pirej nose prednost 4:1!|work=Hrvatska radiotelevizija|access-date=1 July 2018|archive-date=19 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219031320/https://sport.hrt.hr/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41895994|title=Croatia 4–1 Greece|date=9 November 2017|work=BBC Sport|access-date=1 July 2018}}</ref> The 2017–18 squad was known as Croatia's second "golden generation",<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/fifa-world-cup/fifa-world-cup-croatias-new-golden-generation-to-the-rescue/articleshow/64707575.cms|title=FIFA World Cup: Croatia's new golden generation to the rescue|last=Datta|first=Dwaipayan|date=23 June 2018|work=The Times of India|access-date=5 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2018/06/15/croatias-golden-generation-keen-to-live-up-to-expectations/36070241/|title=Croatia's golden generation keen to live up to expectations|date=15 June 2018|work=USA Today|access-date=5 July 2018}}</ref> referencing their 1998 counterparts, during the side's [[1998 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] campaign that year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jun/16/croatia-luka-modric-great-expectations|title=Croatia's Luka Modric: 'It is only right there are great expectations of us'|last=Walker|first=Shaun|date=16 June 2018|website=The Guardian|access-date=1 July 2018|quote=Croatia enter the World Cup on Saturday, their Golden Generation beginning what is surely a last quest towards making an impact on the greatest stage.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/iceland-vs-croatia-world-cup-2018-ivan-rakitic-luka-modric-midfield-tactics-preview-partnership-a8416581.html|title=Are Ivan Rakitić and Luka Modrić the World Cup's biggest unsung heroes?|last=Miller|first=Nick|date=30 June 2018|work=The Independent|access-date=1 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/worldcup/2018/06/30/modric-magic-at-heart-of-croatian-soccers-golden-generation.html|title=Modrić magic at heart of Croatian soccer's golden generation|last=Callaghan|first=Joe|date=30 June 2018|work=Toronto Star|access-date=5 July 2018|quote=The golden generation – with Modrić, Rakitiž and striker Mario Mandžukić as its pillars – have more often watched such efforts go up in flames.}}</ref> They topped [[2018 FIFA World Cup Group D|their group]] with a 2–0 victory over [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/jun/16/croatia-v-nigeria-world-cup-2018-live|title=Croatia 2–0 Nigeria: World Cup 2018 – as it happened|last=Fisher|first=Ben|date=16 June 2018|work=The Guardian|access-date=7 July 2018|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.total-croatia-news.com/sport/29136-world-cup-2018-croatia-1-0-nigeria|title=World Cup 2018: Croatia 2 – 0 Nigeria FT|access-date=7 July 2018|archive-date=25 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221025194820/https://www.total-croatia-news.com/sport/29136-world-cup-2018-croatia-1-0-nigeria}}</ref> a 3–0 win over Argentina,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44439114|title=World Cup 2018: Argentina 0–3 Croatia|date=21 June 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/hrvatska-argentina-hrvati-protiv-messija-i-drustva-na-svjetskom-prvenstvu---516413.html|title=Hrvatska u osmini finala nakon veličanstvene pobjede protiv Argentine: Hrvati pregazili Messija i društvo!|work=Gol.hr|access-date=7 July 2018|language=hr-HR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/argentina-croatia-world-cup-2018-player-ratings-ivan-rakitic-a8410876.html|title=RATINGS: Every player marked out of 10 from Argentina 0–3 Croatia|work=The Independent|access-date=7 July 2018}}</ref> and a 2–1 win against Iceland – their best-ever group stage performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44439256|title=World Cup 2018: Iceland out after defeat by group winners Croatia|date=26 June 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/jun/26/iceland-v-croatia-world-cup-2018-live|title=Iceland 1–2 Croatia: World Cup 2018 – as it happened|last=Burnton|first=Simon|date=26 June 2018|work=The Guardian|access-date=7 July 2018|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

During the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|knockout stage]], they beat Denmark in a penalty shoot-out for the first time<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331498/#match-liveblog|title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia - Matches - Croatia - Denmark |publisher=FIFA|access-date=1 July 2018|archive-date=24 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224181933/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331498/#match-liveblog}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/idemo-hrvatska-igrat-cemo-u-pobjednickim-crnim-dresovima-580341|title=Suba, majstore! Uništio Dance penalima, Vatreni idu na Rusiju|access-date=1 July 2018|language=hr}}</ref> after goalkeeper [[Danijel Subašić]] saved three penalties, equalling the record for most penalties saved in a shoot-out.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44591346|title=World Cup 2018: Croatia beat Denmark on penalties to reach quarter-finals|date=1 July 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=1 July 2018}}</ref> In the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Russia vs Croatia|quarter-finals]], Croatia drew 2–2 with hosts [[Russia national football team|Russia]], becoming the first team since 1990 to win two consecutive penalty shoot-outs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44665444|title=World Cup 2018: Croatia beat hosts Russia 4–3 on penalties to reach semi-final|date=7 July 2018|work=BBC Sport|access-date=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/vatreni-juris-supernapadacka-hrvatska-napada-utvrdu-soci-581226|title=Viva la Vida i Raketa!!! Vatreni kroz rulet penala do polufinala|access-date=7 July 2018|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/jul/07/russia-v-croatia-world-cup-2018-quarter-final-live|title=World Cup 2018: Russia 2–2 Croatia (aet; Croatia win 4–3 on pens) – as it happened|last=Murray|first=Scott|date=7 July 2018|work=The Guardian|access-date=7 July 2018|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Playing England in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Croatia vs England|semi-finals]], Croatia equalized to force their third consecutive extra time, matching the tournament record.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dnevno.hr/sport/nogomet/video-hrvatska-je-u-finalu-svjetskog-prvenstva-herojski-i-povijesni-preokret-u-reziji-mandze-i-perisica-1191909/|title=(VIDEO) Hrvatska je u finalu svjetskog prvenstva! Herojski i povijesni preokret u režiji Mandže i Perišića! |date=11 July 2018|work=Dnevno |access-date=12 July 2018|language=hr-HR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.slobodnadalmacija.hr/sport/domaci-nogomet/clanak/id/555749/hrvatska-u-moskvi-ispisala-nogometnu-povjest-sretna13-drzava-u-finalu-druga-najmanja-na-svijetu|title=Hrvatska u Moskvi ispisala nogometnu povijest: 'sretna' 13. država u finalu, druga najmanja na svijetu|work=Slobodna Dalmacija|access-date=12 July 2018|language=hr-HR}}</ref> [[Mario Mandžukić]] and Perišić scored as Croatia won 2–1 making them the second-smallest country by population (after [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]]) and land area (after the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]]) to reach a [[List of FIFA World Cup finals|World Cup final]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331522/#match-squadlist|title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia - Matches - Croatia - England |publisher=FIFA|access-date=7 July 2018|archive-date=24 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224181921/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331522/#match-squadlist}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jul/11/england-croatia-world-cup-semi-final-match-report|title=England's World Cup dream dashed as Croatia win semi-final in extra time|last=Taylor|first=Daniel|date=11 July 2018|website=The Guardian|access-date=12 July 2018}}</ref> In the [[2018 FIFA World Cup final|final]] they lost to France 4–2, finishing in second place and securing the silver medal.<ref>{{cite news |last=Prince-Wright |first=Joe |date=15 July 2018 |title=France win World Cup after classic final |publisher=[[NBC Sports]] |url=https://soccer.nbcsports.com/2018/07/15/france-win-world-cup-after-classic-final/ |url-status=live |access-date=15 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715193459/https://soccer.nbcsports.com/2018/07/15/france-win-world-cup-after-classic-final/ |archive-date=15 July 2018}}</ref> The match was controversial{{efn|A [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]] was awarded to France for a possible [[Diving (association football)|dive]] by [[Antoine Griezmann]] as well as penalty later in the game awarded by the [[video assistant referee]] (VAR) for a handball by Ivan Perišić.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rappler.com/sports/football/207387-in-photos-the-highest-scoring-fifa-world-cup-since-1966/|title=In Photos: The highest scoring FIFA World Cup finals since 1966|date=15 July 2018|work=Rappler|access-date=15 July 2018|language=en}}</ref>}} for its refereeing.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 July 2018 |title=World Cup 2018: Nestor Pitana's worst day... which saw him suspended |url=https://www.marca.com/en/world-cup/2018/07/15/5b4b3987e2704e3f2f8b4620.html |access-date=1 December 2018 |website=MARCA in English |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Soidri |first=Abdallah |date=15 July 2018 |title=L'arbitre de la finale de la Coupe du Monde raconte sa décision de siffler pénalty pour les Bleus |url=http://footballstories.konbini.com/france/arbitre-finale-coupe-monde-raconte-penalty-bleus/ |access-date=1 December 2018 |website=Football Stories |language=fr-FR}}</ref> The team was welcomed by an estimated half a million people{{efn|The mass gathering amounted to over 10% of the nation's population.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sangupta |first=Varnish |date=2018-07-16 |title=FIFA World Cup 2018: Over 10 percent of population comes out to welcome Croatia's heroes |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/fifa/fifa-world-cup-2018-tens-of-thousands-give-heroes-welcome-to-croatia-team-5262318/ |access-date=2022-12-16 |website=The Indian Express |language=en}}</ref> With 550,000 Croatians present, the event constituted the second-largest gathering in modern Croatia.<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 18, 2022 |title=Modric, 37, sets sights on Nations League title for Croatia |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20221217-modric-37-sets-sights-on-nations-league-title-for-croatia-1 |website=France 24}}</ref> }} at their homecoming in Zagreb.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Chico |first=Harlen |date=July 15, 2018 |title=Croatians watch end of their joyride as thousands crowd Zagreb's central square |language=en-US |newspaper=Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/croatians-ready-to-explode-in-celebration-as-thousands-crowd-central-square/2018/07/15/bbbfa5b4-86e1-11e8-9e06-4db52ac42e05_story.html |access-date=2022-12-16 |issn=0190-8286}}</ref>

The team entered the [[UEFA Nations League|Nations League]]'s inaugural [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League|2018–19 edition]] in [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League A|League A]], along with England and Spain in January 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/zdrijeb-uefa-lige-nacija-koga-hrvatska-moze-izvuci---504034.html|title=Sve što trebate znati o premijernom izdanju novog UEFA-ina natjecanja – Lige nacija!|work=Gol.hr|access-date=1 July 2018|language=hr-HR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/news/0253-0d81efc3a33f-dd2083a5720d-1000--uefa-nations-league-2018-19-league-phase-draw/|title=UEFA Nations League 2018/19 League Phase draw|date=24 January 2018|publisher=UEFA|access-date=1 July 2018}}</ref> Croatia lost 6–0 away to Spain in their first game, the side's record loss in a match.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45489521|title=Spain 6–0 Croatia|work=BBC Sport|date=11 September 2018|access-date=11 September 2018}}</ref> Croatia drew 0–0 home with England,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/oct/12/croatia-v-england-nations-league-live|title=Croatia 0-0 England: Nations League – as it happened|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=12 October 2018|access-date=19 November 2018}}</ref> played behind closed doors due to UEFA sanctions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42874561|title=England's Nations League match in Croatia will be behind closed doors|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=30 January 2018|access-date=19 November 2018}}</ref> In a rematch with the Spanish, Croatia won 3–2 with a goal in stoppage time, followed by a 2–1 away defeat to England.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/nov/15/croatia-spain-nations-league-decider-england-belgium|title=Croatia stun Spain to set up Nations League decider against England|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=15 November 2018|access-date=16 November 2018}}</ref> Croatia were set to be relegated to [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B|League B]] until a tournament rule change retained them in [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League A|League A]], grouping them with Portugal, France and Sweden in the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League|2020–21 tournament]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 September 2019 |title=Promjene u Lige nacija: UEFA "pogurala" Hrvate |url=https://mondo.ba/Sport/Fudbal/a902466/UEFA-Liga-nacija-promjene-u-takmicenju.html |access-date=18 November 2020 |website=Mondo.ba |language=bs}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/idemo-vatreni-srusiti-bilo-bi-divno-srustiti-engleze-na-wembleyju-1283448|title=Preokret Engleza na Wembleyu: Hrvatska ispala iz Lige A|publisher=[[Večernji list]]|date=18 November 2018|access-date=19 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=3 March 2020 |title=Hrvatskoj ždrijeb Lige nacija donio najjaču skupinu i spektakularne utakmice |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/zdrijeb-lige-nacija-uzivo-na-novoj-tv-i-gol-hr-u-prijenos-u-utorak-od-17-30---595359.html |access-date=18 November 2020 |website=Gol.hr |language=hr}}</ref> Croatia lost to France and Portugal, but a victory against Sweden was sufficient to avoid relegation.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Hina |last2=Grgić |first2=Eva |date=11 October 2020 |title=Hrvatska slomila Šveđane u kišom natopljenom Maksimiru |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/od-18-sati-hrvatska-bez-kramarica-na-svedane-u-derutnom-maksimiru-1437677 |access-date=18 November 2020 |website=Večernji list |language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=14 November 2020 |title=Hrvatska drži neslavni rekord u Ligi nacija! Ovaj podatak zvuči gotovo nestvarno za svjetske viceprvake |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/hrvatska-drzi-neslavni-rekord-u-ligi-nacija-ovaj-podatak-zvuci-gotovo-nestvarno-za-svjetske-viceprvake-15031375 |access-date=18 November 2020 |website=Sportske novosti |language=hr-hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Gabelić |first1=Tomislav |last2=Tolić |first2=Josip |date=16 November 2020 |title=Zlatka pitali o smjeni: Znam da ne izgledamo dobro, ali ničega se ne bojim. Bit ćemo opet pravi |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/modric-o-okrsaju-s-ronaldom-728525 |access-date=18 November 2020 |website=24sata |language=hr}}</ref>
