The team topped [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group E|their group]] for the qualifying campaign of [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]],<ref>{{cite news |date=22 March 2019 |title=Anketa Sportskih Novosti: Tko je po Vama bio najbolji protiv Azerbejdžana? Modrić je odigrao kapetanski, ali jedan je igrač rezervirao prvih 11 |newspaper=[[Sportske novosti]] |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/euro2020/anketa-sportskih-novosti-tko-je-po-vama-bio-najbolji-protiv-azerbejdzana-modric-je-odigrao-kapetanski-ali-jedan-je-igrac-rezervirao-prvih-11/8635448 |access-date=25 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323135731/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/euro2020/anketa-sportskih-novosti-tko-je-po-vama-bio-najbolji-protiv-azerbejdzana-modric-je-odigrao-kapetanski-ali-jedan-je-igrac-rezervirao-prvih-11/8635448/ |archive-date=23 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=24 March 2019 |title=Poštenije ne može: Dalić u najkraćem televizijskom obraćanju do sad 'Nismo išli jedan na jedan dok nije ušao Brekalo! Svi drugi idu 200 na sat...' |newspaper=[[Sportske novosti]] |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/nogomet/reprezentacija/postenije-ne-moze-dalic-u-najkracem-televizijskom-obracanju-do-sad-nismo-isli-jedan-na-jedan-dok-nije-usao-brekalo-svi-drugi-idu-200-na-sat/8642735 |access-date=25 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325135944/https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/nogomet/reprezentacija/postenije-ne-moze-dalic-u-najkracem-televizijskom-obracanju-do-sad-nismo-isli-jedan-na-jedan-dok-nije-usao-brekalo-svi-drugi-idu-200-na-sat/8642735/ |archive-date=25 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=24 March 2019 |title=Nema više skrivanja iza srebra. Hrvatska odavno nije ni sjena doprvaka svijeta |publisher=[[Index.hr]] |url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/clanak.aspx?category=sport&id=2073323 |access-date=28 March 2019}}</ref> with a loss to Hungary, and draws against Azerbaijan and [[Wales national football team|Wales]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/euro2020/napokon-je-gotovo-hrvatska-rijetko-videnim-preokretom-izborila-euro-slovaci-su-zabili-a-onda-je-zlatko-dalic-povukao-potez-kvalifikacija/9622936|title=NAPOKON JE GOTOVO, HRVATSKA RIJETKO VIĐENIM PREOKRETOM IZBORILA EURO! Slovaci su zabili, a onda je Zlatko Dalić povukao potez kvalifikacija|date=16 November 2019|publisher=[[Sportske novosti]]|access-date=17 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/dec/02/euro-2020-qualifying-draw-live|title=Euro 2020 qualifying: England face Czech Rep, Germany drawn with Netherlands – as it happened|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=2 December 2018|access-date=3 December 2018}}</ref> The 2020 finals were [[Impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on association football#Continental tournaments|delayed]] to the summer of 2021 due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Europe|COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Conn|first=David|date=17 March 2020|title=Euro 2020 postponed for a year by Uefa because of coronavirus crisis|language=en-GB|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/mar/17/euro-2020-postponed-coronavirus-uefa-champions-league-europa-league|access-date=18 November 2020|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Overall, winning only two out of eight games in 2020, Croatia achieved their worst-ever aggregate win-rate.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Antolić|first=Dražen|date=19 November 2020|title=Najavljivala su se čuda, a Vatreni su 2020. završili s najlošijim godišnjim skorom u povijesti!|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/najavljivala-su-se-cuda-a-vatreni-su-2020-zavrsili-s-najlosijim-godisnjim-skorom-u-povijesti-15032055|access-date=19 November 2020|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=17 November 2020|title=VIDEO: Vatreni herojski pali u drami protiv Portugala, ali ostaju u A skupini Lige nacije!|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/live-hrvatska-portugal-prijenos-je-novoj-tv-i-gol-hr-u---628091.html|access-date=18 November 2020|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref> Croatia finished second in [[UEFA Euro 2020 Group D|their Euros group]],<ref>{{Cite web |agency=[[Croatian News Agency|HINA]] |date=12 November 2020 |title=Napokon se sve zna: Pogledajte tko sve ide na EURO, skupine i raspored utakmica, kada igra Hrvatska... |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/napokon-se-sve-zna-pogledajte-tko-sve-ide-na-euro-skupine-i-raspored-utakmica-kada-igra-hrvatska-15031091 |access-date=18 June 2021 |website=Sportske novosti |language=hr-hr}}</ref> with a 1–0 loss to England, a 1–1 draw with the Czech Republic and a 3–1 win over Scotland. They advanced to the [[UEFA Euro 2020 knockout phase#Croatia vs Spain|round of 16]], where they lost to Spain 5–3 after extra time.<ref>{{cite web |date=28 June 2021 |title=Croatia-Spain UEFA EURO 2020 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/match/2024482/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317164446/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/match/2024482/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |access-date=30 June 2021 |website=UEFA}}</ref> The loss to Spain led to heightened criticism against Dalić and the team by the Croatian public,<ref>* {{Cite web |last=Alač |first=Zvonko |date=28 June 2021 |title=Daliću, hvala za Svjetsko, ali ti si najslabija karika |url=https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dalicu-hvala-za-svjetsko-ali-ti-si-najslabija-karika/2285423.aspx |access-date=1 July 2021 |website=Index.hr |language=hr}}
