* {{cite web |last1=Tironi |first1=Hrvoje |date=29 June 2021 |title=Pogreške Zlatka Dalića koje su nas koštale i ispadanja s Eura... |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/pogreske-zlatka-dalica-koje-su-nas-kostale-i-ispadanja-s-eura-770805 |access-date=3 July 2021 |website=24sata |language=hr}}</ref> Dalić refreshed the team roster by introducing younger debutants for the remainder of [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|World Cup qualifying]] in 2021.<ref>{{cite web |title=Burno ljeto: HNS imao spremnu zamjenu za Dalića, Lovrena htio poslati kući? |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/hns-imao-spremnu-zamjenu-za-dalica-lovren-bio-na-korak-do-izbacivanja---684403.html |website=Gol.hr |access-date=17 November 2021 |language=hr |date=17 November 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Buškulić|first=Ante|date=31 March 2021|title=Dalić otvoreno: Mi nismo ekipa, nismo tim! I to sam im rekao...|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/dalic-otvoreno-mi-nismo-ekipa-nismo-tim-i-to-sam-im-rekao-753873|access-date=18 June 2021|website=24sata|language=hr}}</ref>

Croatia qualified for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 World Cup]] with seven wins, two draws and one loss.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Herljević|first=Bruno|date=2 June 2021|title=SIGURNO NISTE ZAPAZILI: Hrvatska proteklih godina ima nešto što nema niti jedna reprezentacija na svijetu|url=https://net.hr/sport/nogomet/kolumna-iz-voleja-ima-li-hrvatska-reprezentacija-ikakve-sanse-na-europskom-prvenstvu-2020-d4c0b22c-c380-11eb-9cdd-fa357a5390f1|access-date=18 June 2021|website=Net.hr|language=hr-HR}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Ivković |first1=Ivan |title=Najveći hrvatski izbornik u povijesti |url=https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/najveci-hrvatski-izbornik-u-povijesti/2318338.aspx |website=Index.hr |access-date=17 November 2021 |language=hr |date=14 November 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Karin|first=Vice|date=31 March 2021|title=Pobjeda protiv Malte mogla bi dugoročno biti loša za Hrvatsku|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2265159|access-date=18 June 2021|website=Index.hr|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Karin |first1=Vice |title=Dalić je pokazao da uči iz svojih grešaka. Modrić mu je poslao važnu poruku |url=https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dalic-je-pokazao-da-uci-iz-svojih-gresaka-modric-mu-je-poslao-vaznu-poruku/2318492.aspx |website=Index.hr |access-date=17 November 2021 |language=hr |date=15 November 2021}}</ref> The team advanced from [[2022 FIFA World Cup Group F|group stage]] after a 0–0 draw with [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]], a 4–1 win against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]], and finished ahead of Belgium by a single point after drawing 0–0.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Wagner |first=James |date=2022-12-01 |title=Belgium's World Cup Is Over; Morocco and Croatia Advance |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/live/2022/12/01/sports/belgium-croatia-world-cup-scores |access-date=2022-12-10 |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-27 |title=Kramaric hits back at Canada coach after WC win |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37634317/croatia-andrej-kramaric-jibes-canada-boss-world-cup-win |access-date=2022-12-09 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> They won against Japan in a penalty shootout in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Japan vs Croatia|round of 16]] where [[Dominik Livaković]] saved three of four Japanese penalties, equalling a record held by [[Ricardo (footballer, born 1976)|Ricardo]] and Danijel Subašić.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-05 |title=Croatia beat Japan on penalties to reach World Cup quarter-finals – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/dec/05/japan-v-croatia-world-cup-2022-last-16-live-score-updates |access-date=2022-12-09 |website=The Guardian |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Beaton |first=Andrew |title=Croatia Is the World Cup's Penalty Shootout King |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/world-cup-2022-croatia-brazil-penalty-shootout-11670503611 |access-date=2022-12-10 |website=The Wall Street Journal |date=8 December 2022 |language=en-US}}</ref> Croatia similarly beat Brazil during the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Croatia vs Brazil|quarter-finals]] in an upset victory on penalties, having come from behind to draw 1–1 in the final minutes of extra time.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Brazil out of World Cup as Croatia win on penalties|language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63830320 |access-date=2022-12-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Beaton |first=Andrew |title=Brazil Loses to Croatia on Penalty Kicks to Exit the World Cup |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/brazil-croatia-world-cup-2022-neymar-penalty-kicks-11670607307 |access-date=2022-12-10 |website=The Wall Street Journal |date=9 December 2022 |language=en-US}}</ref> In the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Argentina vs Croatia|semi-final]] match, Croatia sustained their heaviest World Cup defeat, 3–0 against Argentina.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Smith |first=Rory |date=2022-12-13 |title=Lionel Messi's World Cup Magic Continues in Argentina's Romp Over Croatia |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/live/2022/12/13/sports/argentina-croatia-world-cup-score |access-date=2022-12-14 |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> They prevailed 2–1 over Morocco in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Third place play-off|third place playoff]], securing their second bronze medal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Morse |first=Ben |date=2022-12-17 |title=Croatia beats Morocco in World Cup third-place playoff match |url=https://www.cnn.com/2022/12/17/football/croatia-morocco-third-place-playoff-2022-world-cup-spt-intl/index.html |access-date=2022-12-17 |website=CNN |language=en}}</ref>

The team topped [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League A#Group 1|their group]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League|2023 Nations League]], knocking out [[2021 UEFA Nations League final|reigning champions]] France by winning 1–0 on a penalty – their first-ever win against the French.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |agency=Reuters |date=2022-06-13 |title=France's Nations League final four hopes vanish with Croatia defeat |language=en |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/frances-nations-league-final-four-hopes-vanish-with-croatia-defeat-2022-06-13/ |access-date=2022-12-14}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=Croatia national football team: record v France |url=https://www.11v11.com/teams/croatia/tab/opposingTeams/opposition/France/ |access-date=2022-12-14 |website=11v11}}</ref> Croatia beat the Netherlands 4–2 in the semi-finals, advancing to their first [[2023 UEFA Nations League final|Nations League final]], against [[Spain men's national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2035581--netherlands-vs-croatia/|title=Netherlands 2–4 Croatia|publisher=UEFA|access-date=15 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=14 June 2023 |title=Croatia reach Nations League final after knocking out hosts Netherlands |language=en |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/croatia-reach-nations-league-final-after-knocking-out-hosts-netherlands-2023-06-14/ |access-date=2023-06-15}}</ref> After drawing the Spanish 0–0 in extra time, the team lost the penalty shootout 4–5, finishing the tournament in second place.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-06-18 |title=Spain win shootout to deny Croatia in Nations League final |language=en |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/spain-win-nations-league-final-penalty-shootout-2023-06-18/ |access-date=2023-06-19}}</ref> Croatia finished second in [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|qualifying]] for [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]], being drawn into a "[[group of death]]" with Spain, Italy, and [[Albania national football team|Albania]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Croatia 1-0 Armenia (Nov 21, 2023) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/655473 |work=[[ESPN]] |access-date=21 November 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Thomas |first=Mark |title=Euro 2024 Draw Unveils Croatia's Challenge in the 'Group of Death' with Spain, Italy, and Albania |url=https://www.thedubrovniktimes.com/news/croatia/item/15750-euro-2024-draw-unveils-croatia-s-challenge-in-the-group-of-death-with-spain-italy-and-albania |access-date=2023-12-12 |website=The Dubrovnik Times |language=en-gb}}</ref> After a 3–0 loss to Spain, they drew 2–2 with Albania and 1–1 with Italy.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Murray |first=Scott |date=2024-06-24 |title=Croatia 1-1 Italy: Euro 2024 – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2024/jun/24/croatia-v-italy-euro-2024-live |access-date=2024-06-27 |work=the Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The Italians eliminated Croatia from advancing to the knockout stage, on points, with a 98th minute stoppage-time goal from striker [[Mattia Zaccagni]].<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Spiers |first1=Tim |last2=Carey |first2=Mark |title=Croatia's Euro 2024 exit marks the end of an era - even for immortals like Luka Modric |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5577860/2024/06/26/modric-croatia-euro-2024-brozovic-kovavic-dalic/ |access-date=2024-06-27 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|2024-25 Nations League]] they finished second in the Group A behind [http://Portugal%20national%20football%20team Portugal] by winning 2 games, drawing 2 and losing 2. In the quarter-finals first game they defeated [[France national football team|France]] at home at [[Stadion Poljud]] but lost in [[Paris]] after penalty shout outs. They overall finished 8th in the whole tournament.

In the qualifiers for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]], they were in a group together with the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]], [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]], [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] and [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]]. They finished first in the group without a single defeat, with 7 wins and 1 draw. Those were the best qualifications of the Croatian national team in history.

==Team image==
===Kits===
{{Commons|Croatia national football team kits}}
[[File:CRO-ENG (17).jpg|thumb|The team's image references the [[Flag of Croatia|national colors of Croatia]]. ''Pictured'': [[Šime Vrsaljko]], 2018]]
Croatia's modern-day team jersey was created in 1990 by [[Miroslav Šutej]], who also designed the current [[coat of arms of Croatia]], which also features in the [[Flag of Croatia|Croatian national flag]]. The red-and-white motif is based on the [[Croatian checkerboard]] ({{lang|hr|šahovnica}}).<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |last=Borden |first=Sam |date=2022-12-08 |title=Why Brazil vs. Croatia is also a battle of iconic kits and deeper meaning |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37634678/brazil-vs-croatia-world-cup-quarterfinal-battle-kits |access-date=2022-12-14 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Knjižnice grada Zagreba – Hrvatski nacionalni simboli|url=http://www.kgz.hr/hr/dogadjanja/hrvatski-nacionalni-simboli/19569|access-date=20 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=GRBOVI I DRESOVI EURA Kako je šahovnica postala simbol Hrvatske |url=http://www.index.hr/tema/euro-2016/grbovi-i-dresovi-eura-kako-je-%C5%A1ahovnica-postala-simbol-hrvatske-i-%C5%A1to-crkva-ima-s-tim-899188 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723192817/http://www.index.hr/tema/euro-2016/grbovi-i-dresovi-eura-kako-je-%C5%A1ahovnica-postala-simbol-hrvatske-i-%C5%A1to-crkva-ima-s-tim-899188 |archive-date=23 July 2017 |access-date=20 July 2017}}</ref> The typical kit color-way features red-and-white checkered shirts, white shorts and blue socks to match the [[Flag of Croatia#Colours|Croatian tricolor]] (''Trobojnica).<ref name=":5" />'' There have been variants made by the kit manufacturers since the original release; the jersey design has remained consistent throughout the years and has served as a blueprint for other Croatian national sports teams and entities.<ref name="nacional.hr" />

The away kits used by the team have for a period been all-blue, incorporating the red-and-white checkers as a trim. Croatia has used darker colored away kits such as the dark navy-and-black checkered design that featured prominently in the 2018 World Cup. The ''Vatreni'' have often been required to use their darker away kits even when playing at home because their opponents have red-and-white color schemes that clash with the chequers of Croatia.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-06-27 |title=World Cup Midweek Mashup – Croatia, 2002 |url=https://museumofjerseys.com/2018/06/27/world-cup-midweek-mashup-croatia-2002/ |access-date=2024-07-14 |website=MuseumofJerseys.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-19 |title=Kit Croatia will wear for all World Cup group matches revealed |url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/kit-croatia-will-wear-for-all-world-cup-group-matches-revealed/ |access-date=2024-07-14 |website=Croatia Week |language=en}}</ref>
