==FIFA ranking history==
The following is a chart of yearly averages of Croatia's [[FIFA Men's World Ranking|FIFA World Ranking]].<ref name=":6">{{cite web |title=The FIFA/Coca-Cola World Ranking - Associations - Croatia - Men's |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifa-world-ranking/CRO |access-date=3 December 2019 |publisher=FIFA}}</ref> Upon admission to FIFA in 1994, Croatia entered the World Ranking at 125th.<ref name=":6" /> Their debut World Cup campaign, during [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]], propelled Croatia to third place after the tournament, marking the fastest ascension in FIFA ranking history.<ref name="Vatreni">{{cite web|url=http://img.fifa.com/worldfootball/ranking/news/newsid=112864.html|title=Croatia eyeing top ten|date=3 March 2007|publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association (FIFA.com)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081206165634/http://img.fifa.com/worldfootball/ranking/news/newsid%3D112864.html|archive-date=6 December 2008|access-date=26 August 2008}}</ref> It hit a then-record [[World Football Elo Ratings|Elo rating]] of 2,006 points in July 1998 and maintained third place until February 1999.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Croatia |url=https://www.eloratings.net/Croatia |access-date=29 March 2026 |website=Elo Ratings |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/ranking/news/newsid=840778.html|title=Croatia follow in golden footsteps|date=7 August 2008|publisher=FIFA|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080826025245/http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/ranking/news/newsid%3D840778.html|archive-date=26 August 2008|access-date=26 August 2008}}</ref> The national team recorded its highest Elo rating in June 2023 with 2,012 points.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Croatia |url=https://www.eloratings.net/ |access-date=2023-06-18 |website=Elo Ratings}}</ref> With an average Elo rating of 1,877 points, Croatia maintains the sixth-highest [[World Football Elo Ratings#Result of match|average rating]] in the world.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Croatia |url=https://www.eloratings.net/ |access-date=2022-12-20 |website=Elo Ratings}}</ref> As of March 2026, Croatia maintains an Elo Rating of 1,944.<ref name=":0" /> They are one of three teams—along with [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] and [[France national football team|France]]—to be named [[FIFA Best Mover of the Year]] more than once, winning the award in 1994 and 1998.<ref>{{cite web |date=19 December 2012 |title=Spain finish 2012 on top, Colombia in fifth |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldranking/news/newsid=1974233/index.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140719093354/http://www.fifa.com/worldranking/news/newsid=1974233/index.html |archive-date=19 July 2014 |access-date=30 July 2014 |publisher=FIFA}}</ref><ref name="croatiamover2">{{cite web |title=FIFA Best Mover of the Year awards |url=https://www.fifa.com/classicfootball/awards/gala/bestmover.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720140712/http://www.fifa.com/classicfootball/awards/gala/bestmover.html |archive-date=20 July 2008 |access-date=23 July 2008 |publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association (FIFA.com)}}</ref><!--Chart updated on Data:Yearly averages of Croatia's FIFA World Ranking.tab (Wikimedia Commons) according to official FIFA records-->
